{META_DATA}: STAR TREK II: THE WRATH OF KHAN
{CHARACTER_NAME}: Written By: Harve Bennett
{META_DATA}: Participating Writers Jack B. Sowards Samuel A. Peeples
{META_DATA}: MAIN TITLE SEQUENCE (TO BE DESIGNED)
{META_DATA}: FADE IN:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 1 BLACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Absolute quiet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOUND bleeds in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Low level b.g. NOISES of Enterprise bridge, clicking of relays, minor electronic effects.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We HEAR A FEMALE VOICE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Captain's log.
{DIALOGUE}: Stardate 8130.3, Starship Enterprise on training mission to Gamma Hydra.
{DIALOGUE}: Section 14, coordinates 22/87/4.
{DIALOGUE}: Approaching Neutral Zone, all systems functioning.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the ANGLE WIDENS, we see the crew at stations; (screens and visual displays are in use): COMMANDER SULU at the helm, COMMANDER UHURA at the Comm Con- sole, DR. BONES McCOY and SPOCK at his post.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Captain is new -- and unexpected.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LT. SAAVIK is young and beautiful.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is half Vulcan and half Romulan.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In appearance she is Vulcan with pointed ears, but her skin is fair and she has none of the expressionless facial immobility of a Vulcan.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: Leaving Section Fourteen for Section Fifteen.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Project parabolic course to avoid entering Neutral Zone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: Aye, Captain.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{META_DATA}: (suddenly)
{DIALOGUE}: Captain... I'm getting something on the distress channel.
{DIALOGUE}: Minimal signal... But something...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Can you amplify?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: I'm trying...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: Course change projected.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: It's an emergency distress call!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: On speakers!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VOICE
{META_DATA}: (filtered, breaking up)
{DIALOGUE}: Imperative!
{DIALOGUE}: Imperative!
{DIALOGUE}: This is the Kobayashi Maru -- nineteen periods out of Altair Six.
{DIALOGUE}: We have struck a gravitic mine and have lost all power... Our hull is...
{META_DATA}: (breaks up, static)
{DIALOGUE}: ... and many casualties.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: This is the Starship Enterprise.
{DIALOGUE}: Your message is breaking up.
{DIALOGUE}: Give your coordinates.
{DIALOGUE}: Repeat --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Enterprise, our position is Gamma Hydra, Section Ten...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: In the neutral zone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Hull penetrated, life support systems failing.
{DIALOGUE}: Can you assist us, Enterprise?
{DIALOGUE}: Can you...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Breaks up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Data on Kobayashi Maru!
{DIALOGUE}: Tactical!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tactical on big screen.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COMPUTER VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Subject vessel is third class neutronic fuel carrier, crew of eighty-one, three hundred passengers.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Damn.
{META_DATA}: (then)
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Sulu, plot an intercept course.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: May I remind the Captain that if a Starship enters the zone --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: I'm aware of my responsibilities, Mister.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{META_DATA}: (with a nod)
{DIALOGUE}: ... Now entering the Neutral Zone...
{META_DATA}: 2 OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 3 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE - ANOTHER ANGLE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COMPUTER VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Warning.
{DIALOGUE}: We have entered the Neutral Zone... Warning...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: Estimating two minutes to intercept.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On screen: Enterprise approaches the stricken vessel.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Stand by transporter room, ready to beam survivors, aboard.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: Captain, I've lost their signal!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COMPUTER VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Alert.
{DIALOGUE}: Sensors indicate three Klingon Cruisers, bearing 316, mark 4, closing fast.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Visual!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On screen we see the approach of the Klingon vessels, they are dark and sinister.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Battle stations!
{DIALOGUE}: Activate shields!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ALARM SOUNDS.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: Shields activated!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Inform the Klingons we are on a rescue mission...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: They're jamming all frequencies, Captain --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COMPUTER VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Klingons on attack course and closing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Screen verifies this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik makes an agonized choice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: We're over our heads.
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Sulu, get us out of here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: I'll try, Captain.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COMPUTER VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Klingon cruisers approaching, bearing 090, mark 20.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Visual!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The image flops: more Klingons approach.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They FIRE photon torpedoes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Evasive action!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sulu does his best, but Enterprise is hit; Sulu is hurled from his station, and Bones hurries to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Engineering!
{DIALOGUE}: damage report!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (INTERCOM)
{DIALOGUE}: Main energizer hit, Captain!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Engage auxiliary power.
{DIALOGUE}: Prepare to return fire!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bridge takes another hit -- a big one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In its wake there is a second electrical EXPLOSION along the communi- cations panel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Uhura falls from her station.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones rushes to her side amid the smoke and alarms.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: A CADET
{DIALOGUE}: Shields collapsing, Captain!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (FILTERED)
{DIALOGUE}: Captain, we're losing auxiliary power!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Fire all phasers...!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: No power to the weapons system, sir.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another hit: reverberating flashes of spark and flame on the bridge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock dies.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones comes to him, but even as he coughs his way through the smoke, a final hit and Bones falls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The room is smoke filled and a shambles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik looks about in shock.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (FILTERED)
{DIALOGUE}: Captain, it's no use.
{DIALOGUE}: We're dead in space.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik digests this for a painful moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then, touch- ing a comm button:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Activate escape pods.
{DIALOGUE}: Send out the Log Buoy... All hands abandon ship.
{DIALOGUE}: Repeat -- all hands --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (FILTERED)
{DIALOGUE}: All right, open her up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a loud CLANGING and --
{META_DATA}: 4 FULL SHOT - ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The side walls of the "bridge" slide apart, revealing a lighted room beyond.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through the opening strides KIRK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stops, surveys the shambles, and shakes his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Any suggestions, Admiral?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Prayer, Mr. Saavik.
{DIALOGUE}: The Klingons do not take prisoners.
{META_DATA}: (to Spock)
{DIALOGUE}: Captain.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Trainees to the briefing room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sulu awakens with a grin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Uhura straightens herself demurely.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Trainees head toward the distant room, Spock rises and leaves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones remains on the floor, head propped in his hand, whimsically.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Physician, heal thyself.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: That's all you have to say?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not a drama critic.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones rolls his eyes and rises.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk sees Saavik who has not moved.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Well, Mr. Saavik, are you going to stay with the sinking ship?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Permission to speak candidly, sir?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Very well.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{META_DATA}: (fights emotion)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't believe this was a fair test of my command capabilities.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: And why not?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Because... there was no way to win.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: A no-win situation is a possibility every commander may face.
{DIALOGUE}: Has that never occurred to you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: ... No, sir.
{DIALOGUE}: It has not.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: How we deal with death is at least as important as how we deal with life, wouldn't you say?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{META_DATA}: (falters)
{DIALOGUE}: As I indicated, Admiral, that thought had not occurred to me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Then you have something new to think about.
{DIALOGUE}: Carry on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She stays at attention.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Wouldn't it be easier to put an experienced crew back on the ship?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: They'll learn.
{DIALOGUE}: Galloping about the cosmos is a game for the young, doctor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leaves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They look at each other.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{META_DATA}: (offended)
{DIALOGUE}: What is that supposed to mean?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HOLD ON Saavik.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 5 INT. CORRIDOR OUTSIDE THE SIMULATOR ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk rounds the corner and sees Spock, leaning against the wall.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (dry)
{DIALOGUE}: Aren't you dead?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock almost smiles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: I assume you are loitering here to learn what efficiency rating I plan to give your cadets.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: I am understandably curious.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They walk together.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: They destroyed the simulator room and you with it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: The Kobayshi Maru scenario frequently wreaks havoc with students and equipment.
{META_DATA}: (dry)
{DIALOGUE}: As I recall you took the test three times yourself.
{DIALOGUE}: Your final solution was, shall we say, unique?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (solemn)
{DIALOGUE}: It had the virtue of never having been tried.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Yours was not a solution which would have occurred to a Vulcan mentality.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: So you said at the time.
{DIALOGUE}: Speaking of which, your prot‚g‚'s first rare -- a trifle emotional --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: She's half Romulan, Jim.
{DIALOGUE}: The admixture makes her more volatile than -- me, for example.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Than you.
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, I see that.
{DIALOGUE}: By the way, thank you for this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He lifts the book.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: I know of your fondness for antiques.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (reads)
{DIALOGUE}: 'It was the best of times, it was the worst of times...' Message, Spock?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: None of which I am consciously aware -- except, of course, happy birthday -- surely the best of times.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk looks around uncomfortably, overlaps:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Hrummm... and where are you off to, now?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: The Enterprise.
{DIALOGUE}: I must check in before your inspection.
{DIALOGUE}: And you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (shortly)
{DIALOGUE}: Home.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock studies him --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Something oppresses you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are old friends --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Something.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He steps into a turbo elevator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The doors close as Spock watches, wiping the scene.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 6 EXT. DEEP SPACE - NEAR CETI ALPHA V
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In f.g. is the U.S.S. RELIANT, an older, somewhat battered starship of the ENTERPRISE class, with a slightly different configuration.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reliant approaches an inhospitable-looking yellow planet: CETI ALPHA V
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Starship log, Stardate 8130.4.
{DIALOGUE}: This report classified MOST SECRET.
{DIALOGUE}: Log Entry by Commander Pavel Chekov, Duty Officer.
{DIALOGUE}: Starship USS Reliant on orbital approach with Ceti Alpha VI in connection with project code name GENESIS.
{DIALOGUE}: We are continuing our search for a lifeless planet which will serve as a suitable test site for the Genesis Experiments.
{DIALOGUE}: This is the 16th planet we have visited, so far, no success.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 7 INT. BRIDGE OF RELIANT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Well-aged and distinctive.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The usual compliment of officers and crew.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAPTAIN CLARK TERRELL, about 45, soft spoken and in good shape, but somewhat laconic.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind Terrell, surveying the data screen is COMMANDER CHEKOV, aged some, but still boyish.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: Standard orbit, Mr. Beach.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BEACH
{DIALOGUE}: Standard orbit, sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: Any change in surface scan?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BEACH
{DIALOGUE}: Negative.
{DIALOGUE}: Limited atmosphere, dominated by craylon gas, sand and high velocity winds.
{DIALOGUE}: Incapable of supporting life forms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forward screen: Ceti Alpha.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: Does it have to be completely lifeless?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell rises and crosses to Chekov.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: Don't tell me you've got something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{META_DATA}: (points)
{DIALOGUE}: We've picked up a minor energy flux reading on one dyno scanner.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: Damn!
{DIALOGUE}: Are you sure?
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe the scanner's out of adjustment --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: I suppose it could be a particle of preanimate matter caught in the matrix...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: All right, let's get on the Comm-pic to Doctor Marcus.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe it's something we can transplant.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: You know what she'll say...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 8 EXT. DEEP SPACE - REGULA I SPACE STATION
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A functional cluster of modules serve as a scientific complex, a futuristic White Sands, orbiting a small barren plantoid in b.g.: Regula.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL MARCUS'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (FILTERED)
{DIALOGUE}: Something you can transplant?
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 9 INT. SPACE STATION - CAROL'S LAB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Big but deserted except for Carol, in contact with Reliant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Surrounded by equipment clearly meant for many workers, CAROL MARCUS is in her early forties, attractive and intelligent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Static mars the trans- missions.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the monitor: Terrell and Chekov, looking hopeful.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: It might only be a particle of preanimate matter...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: Then again it might not.
{DIALOGUE}: You boys have to be clear on this: there can't be so much as a microbe or the show's off.
{META_DATA}: (she thinks)
{DIALOGUE}: Why don't you have a look?
{DIALOGUE}: If it IS something that can be moved...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{META_DATA}: (eager)
{DIALOGUE}: You bet, doctor.
{DIALOGUE}: We're on our way!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carol sighs as the image fades, not happy.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 10 INT. CORRIDOR, SPACE STATION REGULA I
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carol walks through the labyrinthine complex with DAVID, her son, a bright young scientist of twenty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is good looking and humorous.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: How can you let them pull that stuff on you?
{DIALOGUE}: They're just lazy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: And bored.
{DIALOGUE}: I know.
{DIALOGUE}: But maybe it IS something they can...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Come on, Mother, that's just the military mentality.
{DIALOGUE}: Never put off tomorrow what you can put off today.
{DIALOGUE}: If there's one atom of life...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: I know, I know...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silence.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Well, don't have kittens.
{DIALOGUE}: Genesis is going to work.
{DIALOGUE}: They'll remember you in a wreath with Newton, Einstein, Surak...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{META_DATA}: (mock outrage)
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks a lot.
{DIALOGUE}: No respect from my offspring --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Par for the course... you teaming up with me for bridge after dinner?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Every time we have dealings with Starfleet, I get nervous.
{META_DATA}: (shrugs)
{DIALOGUE}: We're dealing with something that COULD be perverted into a dreadful weapon.
{DIALOGUE}: Remember that overgrown boy scout you used to hang out with?
{DIALOGUE}: That's exactly the --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They walk past the CAMERA, their VOICES FADING.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: Listen, kiddo, Jim Kirk was many things, but he was never a Boy Scout...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HOLD ON the empty corridor.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 11 INT. KIRK'S APARTMENT, TERRA - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk reads the novel, trying to focus.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His flat befits an Admiral and a loner with few possessions, except a collection of antiques.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE HEAR A SOFT BONG.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Startled, Kirk lowers the book and pushes a button.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Come.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door slides open and Bones enters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He carries two packages, one of them wrapped in brown paper.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Bless me, doctor; and what beams you into this neck of the woods?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: 'Beware Romulans bearing gifts.'
{DIALOGUE}: Happy Birthday...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With a flourish, he pulls out a bottle of blue liquid.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Romulan Ale!
{DIALOGUE}: Bones, you know this stuff is illegal --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{META_DATA}: (broad)
{DIALOGUE}: I only use it for medicinal purposes.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't be a pring...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (reading the label with difficulty)
{DIALOGUE}: Twenty-two, eighty-three...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Takes the stuff a while to ferment.
{DIALOGUE}: Gimme.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes the bottle and pours; continues talking.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Now open the other one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk starts to obey.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: I'm almost afraid to.
{DIALOGUE}: What did you bring me, contraband Klingon --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: More antiques for your collection -- Cheers!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They drink.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The package is opened: a pair of gold "Ben Franklin" half-glasses.
{META_DATA}: (N.B.: Romulan Ale is an INSTANT DRUNK: both men react.)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Cheers.
{DIALOGUE}: Bones, these are... charming.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Four hundred years old.
{DIALOGUE}: You don't find many with the lens still intact.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Uh -- what are they?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: For your eyes.
{DIALOGUE}: For most patients of your age, I generally administer Retlax Five to restore flexibility of the lens.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: But I'm allergic to Retlax.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Exactly.
{DIALOGUE}: Happy birthday.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He toasts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk is unsure how they work.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Slide them down your nose.
{DIALOGUE}: Now look at me over the top.
{DIALOGUE}: And you read printed matter through the bottom.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (reacts)
{DIALOGUE}: Amazing!
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know what to say --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Say thank you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An awkward silence.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Damn it, Jim, what the hell's the matter?
{DIALOGUE}: Other people have birthdays.
{DIALOGUE}: Why're we treating yours like a funeral?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Bones, I don't want to be lectured.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: What DO you want?
{DIALOGUE}: Damn it, why isn't there a girl here?
{DIALOGUE}: You know this has nothing to do with age.
{DIALOGUE}: This is about you flying a goddamn computer console when you wanna be out hopping Galaxies.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Spare me your notions of poetry, please.
{DIALOGUE}: We all have our assigned duties and...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Bull.
{DIALOGUE}: You're hiding -- hiding behind the rules and regulations --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: And who am I hiding from?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: From yourself, Admiral.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pause.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk pours another drink.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Don't mince words, Bones; tell me what you really think.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{META_DATA}: (mild take)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm your doctor and I'm your friend, Jim.
{DIALOGUE}: Get back your command.
{DIALOGUE}: Get it back before you really do grow old.
{DIALOGUE}: Before you turn into part of this collection.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They look at each other.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 12 EXT. RELIANT - DEEP SPACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: orbiting Ceti Alpha V.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VOICES OVER indicate the transporter room is ready.
{META_DATA}: 13 OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 14 EXT. SURFACE CETI ALPHA V
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A YELLOW PLANET, in constant SWIRLING HURRICANE WINDS OF SAND.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell and Chekov materialize.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their VOICES, filtered, are hard to make out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With the TRICORDER to guide them, they set out...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: Are you sure these are the coordinates?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: Captain, this is the garden spot of Ceti Alpha VI --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: I can hardly see --
{META_DATA}: 15 SEVERAL ANGLES
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The difficult search, the men leaning into the wind --
{META_DATA}: 16 TERRELL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: is ahead of Chekov on a slight rise --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: There's nothing, let's go --
{META_DATA}: 17 ANGLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell waves him frantically forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Chekov moves up, we rise with him to the top of the ridge and look down.
{META_DATA}: 18 ANGLE - THEIR POV
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A RUINED SERIES OF MAN-MADE STRUCTURES, half buried in sand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They look at each other in consternation.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov is worried; something about all this is familiar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They descend towards the structures, now seen to be the wreckage of some sort of space craft.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They pass but do not notice the FEDERATION LOGO, half buried next to their feet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: They look like cargo carriers...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Chekov looks at the porthole, a face suddenly looks back!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is the face of a CHILD!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Apparition scares the daylights out of Chekov -- and us.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He screams.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: What is it?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He comes clumsily over --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: A face!
{DIALOGUE}: I saw -- it was like a child --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He points.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The porthole is empty.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: You're crazy -- !
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: I saw it -- !
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: There's an air-lock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He points and they go into the airlock.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 19 INT. CARGO HOLD
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell and Chekov enter, dumbfounded.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THEIR POV.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Someone lives here -- there are beds, food, all jury- rigged -- but no people.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell checks a monitor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: There's breathable atmosphere in here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes off his helmet; Chekov likewise.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: What the hell is this?
{DIALOGUE}: Did they crash?
{DIALOGUE}: Where's the rest of the ship?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They wander as they talk, picking up objects that be- speak a fairly sophisticated ad hoc environment: a laboratory in one hold; a kitchen; A LARGE SAND TANK filled with disgusting CETI EELS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ABRUPTLY A SOUND -- They start: CHILD'S GURGLE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{META_DATA}: (terrified)
{DIALOGUE}: I told you!
{DIALOGUE}: I told you I saw a --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: Ssssh!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They start looking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They enter a new chamber --
{META_DATA}: 20 KHAN'S QUARTERS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On its side in the sand: the walls are now the floor, etc.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All in crookedness -- like its owner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the floor, smiling at them (i.e., the wall) is a BABY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tentatively they come over to it, looking around --
{META_DATA}: 21 ANGLE - CHEKOV'S POV
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lethal-looking odd swords on one wall, a bookshelf; CAMERA PANS by 20th Century volumes; MOBY DICK, KING LEAR, THE HOLY BIBLE -- and a seat belt dangling with the name on it -- Botany Bay.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov mouths the words, softly at first, then aloud --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: Botany Bay -- oh no!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{META_DATA}: (examines the child)
{DIALOGUE}: What's the matter -- ?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov runs, tries to get his helmet on, tries to drag Terrell --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: Captain, we've got to get out of here -- now!
{DIALOGUE}: Damn!
{DIALOGUE}: Hurry!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell catches his urgency --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: But the child --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: Never mind!
{DIALOGUE}: Hurry!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 22 EXT. CARGO HOLD AIRBAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell and Chekov emerge, helmeted, then stop dead.
{META_DATA}: 23 ANGLE - THEIR POV
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A RING OF SUITED FIGURES has them surrounded.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 24 INT. RELIANT - THE BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Beach, the duty officer, stands looking at Ceti Alpha V on the forward screen.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BEACH
{DIALOGUE}: Try again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KYLE
{DIALOGUE}: Starship Reliant to Captain Terrell ... This is Lieutenant Kyle.
{DIALOGUE}: Will you please respond, Captain... Captain Terrell, respond please.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BEACH
{META_DATA}: (thinks)
{DIALOGUE}: Let's give them a little more time.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 25 INT. CARGO HOLD - CETI ALPHA V
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell and Chekov are held by FOUR STRONG MEN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They seem to be waiting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One of the men is JOACHIM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Out of the airlock steps a tall masked figure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moment of suspense as Terrell and Chekov watch, terri- fied.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mask is peeled back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{META_DATA}: (aloud despite himself)
{DIALOGUE}: Khan!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: KHAN is startled by the recognition; comes over and examines Chekov and Terrell.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (finally)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know you.
{DIALOGUE}: But you.
{DIALOGUE}: I never forget a face.
{DIALOGUE}: Mister Chekov, isn't it?
{META_DATA}: (wonderingly)
{DIALOGUE}: I never thought to see your face again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: Chekov, who is this man?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: A criminal, Captain -- a product of the late 20th Century genetic engineering --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: What do you want with us?
{DIALOGUE}: I demand --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (mild)
{DIALOGUE}: You are in a position to demand nothing, sir.
{DIALOGUE}: I, on the other hand, am in a position to grant nothing.
{DIALOGUE}: What you see is all that remains of the ship's company and the crew of the Botany Bay, marooned here fifteen years ago by Captain James T. Kirk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: Listen to me -- you men and women --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Save your strength, Captain, these people have sworn to live and die at my command two hundred years before you were born.
{DIALOGUE}: Do you mean he...
{META_DATA}: (i.e. Chekov)
{DIALOGUE}: ... never told you the tale?
{DIALOGUE}: To amuse you, Captain?
{DIALOGUE}: Never told you how the Enterprise picked up the Botany Bay, lost in space from the year 1996, myself and the ship's company in cryogenic freeze?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: I've never even met Admiral Kirk --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Admiral?
{DIALOGUE}: He didn't tell you how Admiral Kirk sent seventy of us into exile on this barren sand heap with only the contents of these cargo bays to sustain us?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: You lie!
{DIALOGUE}: On Ceti Alpha V there was life, a fair chance to --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: This is Ceti Alpha V!
{DIALOGUE}: Ceti Alpha VI exploded six months after we were left here.
{DIALOGUE}: The shock shifted the orbit of this planet and everything was laid waste.
{DIALOGUE}: Admiral Kirk never bothered to check on our progress.
{DIALOGUE}: It was only the fact of my genetically engineered intellect that enabled us to survive!
{DIALOGUE}: On earth, two hundred years ago, I was a prince, with power over millions -- now, like Prometheus I have been left by Admiral Kirk to digest my own entrails.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: Captain Kirk was your host!
{DIALOGUE}: You repaid his hospitality by trying to steal his ship and murder him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (moves closer)
{DIALOGUE}: And I'll wager he never told you about his shipmate, the beautiful and courageous Lieutenant McGiver, who gave up everything to join me in exile.
{DIALOGUE}: OUT OF LOVE.
{DIALOGUE}: And see how Admiral Kirk requited her devotion -- She's dead as earth!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The wind howls in the silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: When Khan turns, his eyes are filled with tears.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: A plague upon you all.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He recovers his poise and returns to them --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: You didn't expect to find me.
{DIALOGUE}: You thought this was Ceti Alpha VI.
{DIALOGUE}: Why are you here?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They don't answer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Khan goes over to Terrell and, WITH ONE HAND, LIFTS HIM INTO THE AIR --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Why?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell gasps, stays silent --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: No matter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He lets go; Terrell falls with a thud --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: You will soon tell me willingly enough.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He goes over to the tank and dips a kind of strainer in, pulling out TWO CETI EELS -- wriggling items --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Let me introduce you to Ceti Alpha V's only remaining indigenous life form; what do you think?
{DIALOGUE}: They've killed twenty of my people, including my beloved wife.
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, not all at once and not instantly, to be sure.
{DIALOGUE}: Their young enter through the ears and wrap themselves around the cerebral cortex.
{DIALOGUE}: This has the effect of rendering the victim extremely susceptible to suggestion.
{DIALOGUE}: Later, as they grow, follows madness, paralysis -- and death.
{DIALOGUE}: These are pets, of course -- not quite domesticated.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he speaks, Khan dumps an eel in each of their helmets; he swirls the helmets around as though he were mixing martinis --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: Khan, listen to me!
{DIALOGUE}: Captain Kirk was only doing his duty!
{DIALOGUE}: You --
{META_DATA}: 26 CLOSE UP - KHAN - CAMERA IN
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: There is some pain at first, I am told, and then the effects are quite benign -- until the end.
{DIALOGUE}: That was what I learned from watching my wife.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At a sign, the helmets are slammed down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the muffled shrieks are heard from within, the eels crawl across the faces of Chekov and Terrell; with unerring in- stincts they head for the ears of the two hapless men.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is some atrocious pain as they enter -- then dazed calm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: That's better!
{DIALOGUE}: Now: tell me why you are here -- and tell me where I may find James Kirk.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 27 INT. RELIANT BRIDGE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KYLE
{DIALOGUE}: Captain Terrell.
{DIALOGUE}: Captain Terrell... This is Reliant; please respond.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No answer -- Beach makes up his mind --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BEACH
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Kyle, muster a landing party with full arms.
{DIALOGUE}: Alert the transporter room.
{DIALOGUE}: We're beaming down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He heads for the door but is stopped by:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (filtered)
{DIALOGUE}: Reliant, this is Terrell.
{DIALOGUE}: Respond please.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BEACH
{DIALOGUE}: This is Reliant.
{DIALOGUE}: Clark, are you all right?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fractional pause.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (filtered)
{DIALOGUE}: Everything's fine, commander.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll explain when I see you.
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, by the way, we're bringing several guests aboard.
{DIALOGUE}: Prepare to beam up on my next signal.
{DIALOGUE}: Terrell out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beach and Kyle look at each other.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KYLE
{DIALOGUE}: Guests?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BEACH
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe we ARE transplanting something.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 28 EXT. ORBITING SPACE DOCK AREA - TERRA (FEATURE STOCK)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SPACE SHUTTLE moving toward us.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 29 INT. SPACE SHUTTLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A new composite.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones, Sulu, Uhura and Kirk -- who sits, reading.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through the windows we can see the approach to the starship ENTERPRISE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk looks up, nods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sulu activates a comm button.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: Enterprise, this is Admiral Kirk's party on final approach.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ENTERPRISE VOICE
{META_DATA}: (filtered)
{DIALOGUE}: Enterprise welcomes you.
{DIALOGUE}: Prepare for docking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk looks up from his book as Sulu sits next to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: I really must thank you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{META_DATA}: (embarrassed)
{DIALOGUE}: I am delighted; any chance to go aboard Enterprise, however briefly, is always an excuse for nostalgia.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: I cut your new orders personally.
{DIALOGUE}: By the end of the month, you'll have your first command: USS EXCELSIOR.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you, sir.
{DIALOGUE}: I've looked forward to this for a long time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: You've earned it.
{DIALOGUE}: But I'm still grateful to have you at the helm for three weeks.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't believe these kids can steer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sulu laughs.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 30 EXT. SPOCE DOCK - TERRA (FEATURE STOCK)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shuttle approaches the mammoth airstrip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As we near the ship, a few WORK CREWS IN SPACE flit about her hull, working.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 31 EXT. ENTERPRISE (FEATURE STOCK)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shuttle makes its way to the Docking Lock of the mother ship and settles in place.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 32 INT. ENTERPRISE DOCKING BAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A reception group awaits, led by Captain Spock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik stands at his side, in company of the Trainee crew.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Also present: CHIEF ENGINEER MR. SCOTT and members of his staff in their distinctive uniforms.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: INTERCOM VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Docking procedure complete.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Prepare for Admiral's inspection.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The group comes to attention.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Open the Air Lock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The doors open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk and his staff are piped aboard by an electronic version of the boatswain's tradi- tional whistle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk salutes the Federation symbol and steps forward to exchange salutes with Spock.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Permission to come aboard, Captain?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Welcome aboard, Admiral.
{DIALOGUE}: I believe you know my trainee crew.
{DIALOGUE}: Certainly they have come to know you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (dryly to Saavik)
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, we've been through death and life together.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik stiffens slightly -- humor is not her forte.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing to Scotty)
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Scott, you old space dog.
{DIALOGUE}: You're well?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY
{DIALOGUE}: I had me a wee bout -- but Dr. McCoy pulled me through.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Oh?
{DIALOGUE}: A wee bout of what, Mr. Scott?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Uncomfortable, Scotty exchanges a glance with Bones --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Shore leave, Admiral.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Ah.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stops before a BRIGHT-FACED FOURTEEN-YEAR OLD, stand- ing so stiff he looks like he'll break -- in an engineer's uniform.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: And who is this?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRESTON
{META_DATA}: (breathless)
{DIALOGUE}: Midshipman First Class Peter Preston, engineers mate, SIR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A big salute.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk is amused, returns the salute.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Your first training voyage, Mr. Preston?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRESTON
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, SIR.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: I see.
{DIALOGUE}: Well, shall we start with the engine room?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He moves, followed by his staff.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY
{META_DATA}: (eyeing his prot‚g‚)
{DIALOGUE}: I believe you'll find all in order --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: We'll see you on the bridge, Admiral.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Very good, Mr. Spock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk and party leave.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA PUSHES IN ON SPOCK AND SAAVIK.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: He's not what I expected, Sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: What did you expect, Lieutenant?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{META_DATA}: (uncertain)
{DIALOGUE}: He's very human.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: We can't all be perfect, Saavik.
{DIALOGUE}: You must control your prejudices and remember that as a Vulcan as well as a Romulan you are forever a stranger in an alien land.
{DIALOGUE}: Around you are humans, and as a member of the Starfleet you are unlikely ever to escape their presence or their influence.
{DIALOGUE}: You must learn to tolerance in addition to all else I have taught you.
{DIALOGUE}: Tolerance is logical.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik is humbled.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: As always, my mentor.
{DIALOGUE}: Company dismiss.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 33 INT. ENTERPRISE ENGINE ROOM - LOOKING DOWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The inspection party dwarfed by the size.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silence as Kirk looks around, runs a finger for dust, etc.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Scotty, his team and Preston, stand at attention.
{META_DATA}: 34 ANGLE - FLOOR OF ENGINE ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FEATURING power room separated by glass from the rest of the facilities.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones, Sulu, Uhura, and some train- ees watch as Kirk inspects one console, clearly the responsibility of the bursting Midshipman Preston.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRESTON
{META_DATA}: (blurting)
{DIALOGUE}: I believe you'll find everything shipshape, Admiral.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (sternly puts him on)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh do you?
{DIALOGUE}: Have you any idea, Midshipman Preston, how many times I've had to listen to Mr. Scott on the Comm, telling me his troubles?
{DIALOGUE}: Have you any idea the ribbing I've had to endure in the officers' mess to the effect that the Enterprise is a flying death trap?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRESTON
{META_DATA}: (scandalized)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, no, sir!
{DIALOGUE}: This is the finest engine room in the whole Star --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The repressed grins of the others, and a smile on Scotty's face tell Preston he's being had.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stops, confused.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRESTON
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: If the Admiral can't see the facts for himself, then, with all due respect, he's as blind as a Tiberion bat.
{DIALOGUE}: SIR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Approving laughter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk looks amused.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Midshipman, you're a tiger.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY
{DIALOGUE}: My sister's youngest, Admiral.
{DIALOGUE}: Crazy to get to space.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Every young boy's fancy.
{DIALOGUE}: I seem to remember it myself.
{META_DATA}: (brisk)
{DIALOGUE}: Very well.
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Scott, are your engines capable of handling a minor training cruise?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY
{DIALOGUE}: Give the word, Admiral.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Scott, the word is given.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY
{DIALOGUE}: Aye, sir.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He moves off, followed by Preston, who gives one last salute as Kirk leaves, followed by Bones.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{META_DATA}: (dry)
{DIALOGUE}: What about the rest of the inspection, Admiral?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: The inspection will continue once we're underway, Doctor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They step into the Turbo Lifts.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 35 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The real one, no doubt!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA REVEALS the maze detail: winking and blinking displays, all HANDS at station, a hum of activity, Uhura and Sulu in familiar chairs, Spock is in the Captain's chair, Saavik in the First Officer's position.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk and Bones stand towards the rear.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: INTERCOM VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: This is Starfleet operations.
{DIALOGUE}: Enterprise is cleared for departure.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: Admiral on the bridge!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Very well, Mr. Saavik, clear all moorings.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Aye, sir.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik punches data into her console.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 36 EXT. SPACE DOCK AND ENTERPRISE (FEATURE STOCK)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The dock slowly folds away from the ship.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 37 INT. BRIDGE, ENTERPRISE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik watches instruments, punches data in response.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: All moorings are clear, Captain.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you, Mr. Saavik.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock casts a glance at Kirk, then, to Saavik:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Lieutenant, how many times have you piloted a Starship out of Spacedock?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Never, sir.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk tries to conceal his reaction.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock enjoys it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Take her out, Mr. Saavik.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Aye, sir.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik settles herself in the chair, looks again at the console -- Spock looks at Kirk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: There's a first time for everything, Admiral.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (casual)
{DIALOGUE}: To be sure, Captain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They all stifle their responses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk is like a father watching his kid drive the family car for the first time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Aft thrusters, Mr. Sulu.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: Aft thrusters, sir.
{META_DATA}: 38 OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 39 EXT. ENTERPRISE (FEATURE STOCK)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as the ship slowly and majestically leaves the dock.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 40 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Activity hums.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Ahead one quarter impulse power.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk starts to say something, but doesn't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones looks at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{META_DATA}: (sotto voice)
{DIALOGUE}: Would you like a tranquilizer?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk shakes his head, takes a breath --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: Ahead one quarter impulse power.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 41 EXT. SPACE DOCK ENTERPRISE (FEATURE STOCK)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ship clears the dock and begins heading into space.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 42 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk quietly lets his breath out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: We are clear and free to navigate.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Course heading, Captain?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock turns inquiringly to Kirk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Captain's discretion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock digests this with a slight smile.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Sulu, you may follow your nose.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 43 EXT. THE ENTERPRISE (STOCK FROM FEATURE)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She gathers speed into the vastness of space.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 44 EXT. SPACE, FEATURING THE RELIANT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: moving towards us, in opposition to the previous shot, close enough for us to read her markings.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 45 INT. RELIANT BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Khan occupies the Captain's chair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We PULL BACK: the crew of the RELIANT has been replaced by Khan's fol- lowers in their odd-looking clothes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At the helm is Joachim, Khan's lieutenant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is in the largest and brightest of Khan's group.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell sits in the First Officer's chair, Chekov at the Comm Console.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their behavior is normal, save for subtle hesitation, symptoms of their mind-controlled state.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOACHIM
{DIALOGUE}: Steady on course.
{DIALOGUE}: All systems normal.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: It's not much different from Enterprise.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: When I was a guest aboard her some years ago, Captain Kirk kindly allowed me to memorize her technical manuals.
{DIALOGUE}: And now, Mr. Chekov, let us review: You say you have no details of Project 'Genesis' ?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: Beyond what I told you, sir, it is classified information.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Umm.
{DIALOGUE}: And would Admiral Kirk have access to such information?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: I would think so, sir.
{DIALOGUE}: He's on the Fleet General Staff.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Then to whom do you report directly regarding Genesis?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: To Doctor Marcus, the civilian director of the experiments on Space Laboratory Regula I.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (thinks)
{DIALOGUE}: I see.
{DIALOGUE}: Helmsman?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELMSMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Aye, sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOACHIM
{DIALOGUE}: May I speak?
{DIALOGUE}: We're all with you, sir, but consider: we are free, we have a ship and the means to go where we will.
{DIALOGUE}: We have escaped permanent exile on Ceti Alpha V.
{DIALOGUE}: You have proved your superior intellect and defeated the plans of Admiral Kirk.
{DIALOGUE}: You do not need to defeat him again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: He tasks me -- and I'll have him.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll chase him round the moons of Nibia and round the Antares maelstrom and round perdition's flames before I give him up.
{META_DATA}: (as no one speaks)
{DIALOGUE}: Prepare to alter course -- for Space Station Regula I.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 46 EXT. SPACE - SPACE STAION REGULA I
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 47 INT. CAROL'S LAB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Huge and busy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Among the scientists going about their tasks are JEDDA, a Deltan; MARCH, thin intense; MADISON, black, easy going.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are all young and earnest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carol and David huddle over a computer console.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Does that about do it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: I don't think there's another piece of information we could squeeze into the memory banks.
{DIALOGUE}: Next time, we'll design a bigger one.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Who --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jedda at the Comm Console overlaps.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JEDDA
{DIALOGUE}: Comm-Pic coming in on hyperchannel ... It's Reliant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carol moves forward as the others close in.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: On the screen, please, Jedda.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Buttons punched; the screen ebbs, flows and crackles on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON SCREEN is CHEKOV.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: ... come in, please.
{DIALOGUE}: This is Reliant calling Regula I. Repeat.
{DIALOGUE}: This is USS Reliant --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: Commander, we are receiving.
{DIALOGUE}: This is Regula I. Go ahead.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: Dr. Marcus... good.
{DIALOGUE}: We're en route to you and should be there in three days.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: En route?
{DIALOGUE}: Why?
{DIALOGUE}: We weren't expecting you for another three months.
{DIALOGUE}: Has something happened?
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Has something happened?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you read us?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{META_DATA}: (fractional pause)
{DIALOGUE}: All went well.
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing has happened.
{DIALOGUE}: Ceti Alpha VI has checked out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pleased reaction from the scientists.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: I still don't under --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: We have received new orders.
{DIALOGUE}: Upon our arrival at Regula I, all materials of Project Genesis will be transferred to this ship for immediate testing at Ceti Alpha VI.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Consternation in the lab.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: David is livid -- the words "Bullshit" are overlapped by his mother.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: Will you please be quiet!
{META_DATA}: (back to console)
{DIALOGUE}: Commander Chekov, this is completely irregular.
{DIALOGUE}: Who gave the order you are quoting?
{DIALOGUE}: Who gave the order?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{META_DATA}: (still smiling)
{DIALOGUE}: The order comes from Starfleet command, Dr. Marcus, direct from the General Staff.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: But Genesis is a civilian project, under my control --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: I have my orders.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Pin him down, mother!
{DIALOGUE}: Who gave the orders!?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov hesitates, seems to be listening to someone off the monitor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: The orders come from Admiral James T. Kirk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sensation in the lab.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: I knew it!
{DIALOGUE}: I knew it!
{DIALOGUE}: All along the military has wanted to get their hands on this --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He starts to press a button; Carol pushes his hand away and communicates herself.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: This is completely improper, Commander Chekov.
{DIALOGUE}: I have no intention of allowing Reliant or any other unauthorized personnel access to our work or materials.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{META_DATA}: (pauses; listens)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry you feel that way, Doctor.
{DIALOGUE}: Admiral Kirk's orders are confirmed.
{DIALOGUE}: Please prepare to deliver Genesis to us upon our arrival.
{DIALOGUE}: Reliant out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The image fades.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: Commander Chekov -- !
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 48 INT. BRIDGE OF RELIANT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov, in a matched cut, turns away as CAMERA WIDENS TO REVEAL KHAN by his side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is charming.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Well done, Commander.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: You realize, sir, that they will attempt to contact Admiral Kirk and confirm the order.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Khan smiles, more charming than ever as we move in.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 49 INT. REGULA I LAB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Everyone is talking at once.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: Will you please be quiet!
{DIALOGUE}: We must have order here.
{META_DATA}: (as they subside)
{DIALOGUE}: This has to be some sort of mistake.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Mistake?
{DIALOGUE}: We're all alone here.
{DIALOGUE}: They waited until everyone was on shift-leave to do this.
{DIALOGUE}: Reliant is supposed to be at our disposal, not vice-versa.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MADISON
{DIALOGUE}: It seems clear that Starfleet never intended that --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: I know, but --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: I've tried to warn you.
{DIALOGUE}: Scientists are always pawns of the military --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{META_DATA}: (angry)
{DIALOGUE}: Starfleet has kept the peace for a hundred years, I cannot and will not subscribe to your interpretation of this event.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silence.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JEDDA
{META_DATA}: (Deltan cool)
{DIALOGUE}: You may be right, Doctor, but what about Reliant?
{DIALOGUE}: She's on her way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carol reacts: this is certainly true.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: Get your gear together where it's handy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARCH
{DIALOGUE}: Where are we going?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: That's for us to know and Reliant to find out.
{DIALOGUE}: We have only three days.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's not waste time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They split off in different directions as ordered.
{META_DATA}: 50 OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 51 EXT. SPACE - ENTERPRISE (FEATURE STOCK)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In no particular hurry.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 52 INT. ENTERPRISE CORRIDOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk waits for the Turbo Lift, which opens at last.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he gets in --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Hold please -- !
