{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 57 EXT. SPACE - ENTERPRISE (FEATURE STOCK)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ship accelerates, and then, with an eye-filled burst, whips ahead to warp speed, disappearing.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 57A INT. SPOCK'S QUARTERS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock is at meditation as Kirk enters quietly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock looks up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: We've got a problem.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock raises an eyebrow --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Something may be wrong at Regula I. We've been ordered to investigate.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Regula I is a scientific research laboratory, if memory serves...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: I told Starfleet all we had was a boatload of children but we're the only ship in the quadrant.
{DIALOGUE}: Spock: those cadets of yours -- how good are they?
{DIALOGUE}: How will they respond under real pressure?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Like all living beings, Admiral each according to his gifts.
{DIALOGUE}: The ship is yours.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: That won't be necessary: just take me to Regula I.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Excuse my presumption, but I do not agree.
{DIALOGUE}: As a teacher on a training mission, I am content to command a Starship.
{DIALOGUE}: If we are to go on actual duty, it is clear that the senior officer aboard must assume command.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: But it may be nothing; garbled communications.
{DIALOGUE}: Why don't you...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: You proceed from a false assumption.
{DIALOGUE}: I am a Vulcan.
{DIALOGUE}: I have no ego to bruise.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk smiles in bemused wonderment.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: You are going to remind me that logic alone dictates your actions.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: I was going to remind you of nothing, least of all that which you know well.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Your mistake, if I may be so bold, was promotion.
{DIALOGUE}: Commanding a Starship is your first best destiny.
{DIALOGUE}: Anything else is a waste of material.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: I would not presume to debate you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: That is wise.
{DIALOGUE}: In any case, were I to invoke logic, logic clearly dictates that the needs of the many outweigh the needs of the few.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Or the one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock inclines his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: You are my superior officer.
{DIALOGUE}: You are also my friend.
{DIALOGUE}: I have been and always shall be yours.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk is moved.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He starts to speak, can't -- finally:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Will you accompany me to the bridge?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: I'd best talk with Mr. Scott, first so that he may, in his own words, explain the situation to his cadets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk's face tells us the wisdom of Spock's choice.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 58 EXT. SPACE STATION REGULA I
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Floating quietly around the planet below.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tranquil as we PUSH SLOWLY IN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OVER we can hear, FILTERED, UHURA'S VOICE:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Regula I, this is Enterprise.
{DIALOGUE}: This is Enterprise calling.
{DIALOGUE}: Do you receive... I say...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 59 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Featuring Spock and Uhura, as she keeps trying --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: ... Again, this is Enterprise calling Space Lab Regula I. Come in, please.
{DIALOGUE}: Dr. Marcus.
{DIALOGUE}: Please respond, please -- it's no use; no response from Regula I.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: But no longer jammed?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: No, sir.
{DIALOGUE}: No nothing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock considers, moves to Kirk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: There are two possibilities, sir they are unwilling to respond, they are unable to respond.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: How far?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Twelve hours and forty-three minutes, present speed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Give up Genesis, she said.
{DIALOGUE}: What in God's name does that mean?
{DIALOGUE}: Give it up to whom?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: It might help my analysis if I knew what Genesis was.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk looks at him, nods; rising now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Uhura, ask Dr. McCoy to join us in my quarters.
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Saavik, take the con.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They start for the Turbo Lifts as Saavik reacts --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 60 INT. KIRK'S QUARTERS
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: I've got the sick bay ready.
{DIALOGUE}: Will someone please tell me what is going on?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (dims lights)
{DIALOGUE}: Computer.
{DIALOGUE}: Request security procedure and access to Project Genesis Summary.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COMPUTER VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Identify for retina scan.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Kirk, Admiral James T., Starfleet General Staff.
{DIALOGUE}: Security Class 1.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The screen is suddenly busy with coded read-outs and then computer graphics of retina patterns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then it glows green.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SECURITY CLEARANCE, CLASS 1 GRANTED.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Summary, please.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: More coded read-outs, a red line SECURITY SCAN, then over it APPROVED, in green.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Replaced by:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 61 ON SCREEN INT. CAROL MARCUS' LAB, REGULA I
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carol appears, FACING CAMERA, not used to it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: To one side stands David and behind them, the lab.
{META_DATA}: 62 ANGLE - KIRK, SPOCK, BONES
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Carol Marcus --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{META_DATA}: 63 ON SCREEN (AND INTERCUT)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: I'm Dr. Carol Marcus, and I am the director of the Project Genesis team at Regula I.
{DIALOGUE}: What exactly IS Genesis?
{DIALOGUE}: Put simply, Genesis is a procedure whereby the molecular structure of any given matter can be restructured -- changed -- into anything else of identical mass.
{META_DATA}: (DNA ILM TAPE ACCOMPANIES, AD LIB)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Fascinating.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Wait --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: Stage One of our experiments was conducted in the labora- tory.
{DIALOGUE}: Stage Two of the series will be attempted in a lifeless underground; Stage Three will involve the process on a plane- tary scale.
{DIALOGUE}: What follows is a computer projected simulation of Stage Three.
{DIALOGUE}: Please watch closely.
{META_DATA}: 64 ILM MONITOR SEQUENCE &amp; &amp;
{CHARACTER_NAME}: 65 CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: It is our intention to introduce what we call the Genesis device or "torpedo" into the targeted area of a lifeless space body, a moon or other inert form -- the device is fired --
{META_DATA}: 66 ON BONES, SPOCK AND KIRK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: react with wonder.
{META_DATA}: 67 BACK TO MONITOR
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: -- Unleashing, almost instantan- eously, what we call the Genesis effect.
{DIALOGUE}: Particulate matter is reorganized and electrified -- with life introduced results.
{DIALOGUE}: Instead of a dead moon, a living breathing planet, capable of sus- taining whatever life forms we see fit to deposit on it... The reformed object you see represents the merest fraction of the Genesis potential, should the Federation wish to pursue these experiments to their logical conclusion.
{META_DATA}: 67A BACK TO CAROL IN LAB
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: When we consider the problems of population and food supply, the usefulness of this process begins to become clear.
{DIALOGUE}: This concludes this demonstration tape.
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you for your attention.
{DIALOGUE}: The Genesis team eagerly awaits the decision of the Federation regarding the next phase of our work.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tape becomes snowy and blinks off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk looks at Bones and Spock -- they are stunned.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: It literally is Genesis...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: The power of creation --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Have they proceeded with their experiments?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: The tape was made a year ago.
{DIALOGUE}: I can only assume they've reached Phase Two by now --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: But dear Lord, are we intelligent enough to -- Suppose, this thing were used where life already exists?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: It would destroy such life in favor of its new matrix --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: It's new -- have you any idea what you're saying?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: I was not attempting to evaluate its moral implications, Doctor.
{DIALOGUE}: As a matter of cosmic history, it has always been easier to destroy than to create --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Not anymore!
{DIALOGUE}: Now you can do both at the same time!
{DIALOGUE}: According to myth, the earth was created in six days.
{DIALOGUE}: Watch out: here comes Genesis; we'll do it for you in six minutes --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: I don't dispute that in the wrong hands --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Would you like to tell me whose are the right hands, my cold-blooded friend?
{DIALOGUE}: Are you in favor of these experiments?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Gentlemen, this isn't --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Really, Dr. McCoy; you cannot ban the acquisition of knowledge because you distrust the moral implications of what you learn.
{DIALOGUE}: Logic suggests --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Logic??
{DIALOGUE}: We're talking about universal Armageddon, you inhuman bloodless...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (intercom)
{DIALOGUE}: Admiral, sensors indicate a vessel in our area, closing fast.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: What do you make of her?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: It's one of ours, Admiral... It's Reliant.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: What's she doing here?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Chekov's on Reliant, isn't he?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 68 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The whoosh of the turbo doors and Kirk, Bones and Spock assume their posts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik stands next to Kirk's chair.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: She's not responding...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Try the emergency channels...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: Enterprise to Reliant.
{DIALOGUE}: Come in, Reliant.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Picture, Mr. Saavik.
{META_DATA}: 69 ANGLE INCLUDING THE FORWARD SCREEN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Space; a tiny dot in the distance, growing larger.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Attempt visual communication.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Is it possible their COMM system has failed -- ?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: It would explain a great many things --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 70 EXT. SPACE - THE RELIANT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boring forward ominously.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 71 INT. BRIDGE - THE RELIANT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Khan and his crew; no sign of Chekov and Terrell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On Khan's screen, the Enterprise grows larger --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (almost sing-song with joy)
{DIALOGUE}: Slow to one-half impulse power.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's be friends...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELMSMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Slowing to one-half impulse.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOACHIM
{DIALOGUE}: They're requesting visual communications, sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Let them eat static.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOACHIM
{DIALOGUE}: They're still running with shields down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Of course.
{DIALOGUE}: We're one big happy fleet.
{DIALOGUE}: Ah, Kirk, my old friend, do you know the Klingon proverb that tells us revenge is a dish that is best served cold?
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: It is very cold in space.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 72 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: Reliant in our section this quadrant, sir, and slowing --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Visual.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Visual of Reliant appears.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Sir, may I quote General Order 12: 'On the approach of any vessel, when communications have not been est --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Lieutenant, the Admiral is aware of the Regulations.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Aye, sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (watches the screen)
{DIALOGUE}: This is damned peculiar.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Yellow alert.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Energize defense fields.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ALARMS SOUND.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The lights on the bridge dim into the soft reddish glow of battle illumination.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ADDITIONAL CREW troop in to man vacant consoles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: I'm getting a voice message... wait ... short range band.
{DIALOGUE}: They say their Chambers coil is shorting their COMM system.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Spock?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Scanning...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He steps to his station.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 73 EXT. SPACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two ships are very close, barely moving as they inch toward each other.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 74 INT. RELIANT BRIDGE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOACHIM
{DIALOGUE}: They still haven't raised their shields.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Khan is half out of his seat, sweating with anticipation.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Careful: Not all at once.
{DIALOGUE}: The engine room.
{DIALOGUE}: Lock on target and prepare to fire.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOACHIM
{DIALOGUE}: Locking phasers on target.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Computer graphics monitor: Cross-hairs on Enterprise.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BIG SCREEN (?)
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 75 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE - FAVORING SPOCK
