{DIALOGUE}: Khan!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Who?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: You still remember, Admiral.
{DIALOGUE}: I cannot help but be touched.
{DIALOGUE}: Of course, I remember you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: What is the meaning of this attack?
{DIALOGUE}: Where is the crew of the Reliant?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Surely I have made my meaning plain.
{DIALOGUE}: I mean to avenge myself upon you, Admiral.
{DIALOGUE}: I've deprived your ship of power and when I swing round I mean to deprive you of your life --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 88 EXT. SPACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We can see Reliant making a large arc as she prepares to come back for another round.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 89 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (on screen)
{DIALOGUE}: -- But I wanted you to know first who it was who had beaten you: I, Khan Noonian Singh, the eagle you attempted to cage forever.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Khan, listen to me -- if its me you want, I'll have myself beamed aboard.
{DIALOGUE}: All I ask is that you spare my crew.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: That is a most intriguing offer.
{DIALOGUE}: Typical, I must say of your sterling character.
{DIALOGUE}: Let me think.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 90 EXT. SPACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reliant continues her slow arc.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 91 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (on screen)
{DIALOGUE}: I make you a counter-proposal, I will agree to your terms, if in addition to yourself, you turn over to me all data and material regarding the project called Genesis.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reactions from Spock and Kirk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Genesis, what's that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
