{DIALOGUE}: Reliant's command...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: HURRY.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: The prefix code?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: It's all we've got.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: On screen...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (to Khan)
{DIALOGUE}: We're finding it.
{META_DATA}: (urging)
{DIALOGUE}: Please, please -- you've got to give us time -- the bridge is smashed, computers inoperative...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Time is a luxury you do not have, Admiral: forty-five seconds...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 92 EXT. SPACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reliant, her arc completed, is coming back.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 93 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: I don't understand --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk puts on his spectacles --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: You've got to learn WHY things work on a Starship.
{META_DATA}: (to Khan)
{DIALOGUE}: It's coming through now, Khan...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{META_DATA}: (descends)
{DIALOGUE}: The prefix code is 16309.
{DIALOGUE}: All commands from each Starship bridge are relayed electronically; each ship has its own prefix combination code...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Thirty seconds...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: ... to prevent an enemy from doing just what we're attempting; using our console to tap in a message, an order to lower Reliant's damn shields...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{META_DATA}: (at the weapons console)
{DIALOGUE}: Let's hope he hasn't changed the combination.
{DIALOGUE}: He's quite intelligent...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (grim)
{DIALOGUE}: Wait for my signal, Spock -- too soon and he'll have time to figure it out and raise them again.
