{DIALOGUE}: No!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOACHIM
{DIALOGUE}: Sir, we must!
{META_DATA}: (desperate urging)
{DIALOGUE}: We must repair the damage.
{DIALOGUE}: Enterprise will wait; she's not going anywhere.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Khan calms as the other holds him; he breathes deeper.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 101 EXT. SPACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reliant turns away.
{META_DATA}: 102 ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They watch on screen as Reliant hauls off.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{META_DATA}: (breathless)
{DIALOGUE}: Sir, you did it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (enraged)
{DIALOGUE}: I did nothing -- except get caught with my britches down.
{DIALOGUE}: I must be senile.
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Saavik, you just keep right on quoting regulations.
{DIALOGUE}: Meantime, let's find out what the hell is going on and see how bad we've been --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The turbo doors whoosh open as Kirk reaches them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Scotty stands there, tears streaming down his face; he holds the body of Midshipman Preston.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Both of them are covered in blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sways into Kirk's arms as the others rush forward.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 103 EXT. SPACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Enterprise, motionless, scars of battle showing.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 104 INT. ENGINE ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The CREW, wearing respirators amid the motionless ball of gas, work frantically at a dozen jobs, trying to put things aright, splicing wires, etc.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Some TRAINEES who panicked are back.
{META_DATA}: 105 FEATURE THE CREW CHIEF
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: making a final adjustment.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CREW CHIEF
{DIALOGUE}: Hit your blowers!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A TURBO WHINES and a great wind of suction pulls the gas towards appropriate vents.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Crew Chief watches, then yanks off his respirator; wipes his brow.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 106 INT. SICK BAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MANY CASUALTIES IN EVIDENCE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk enters and LEADS CAMERA THROUGH them; he has a word or two for men he doesn't know by name.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk leads us to the operating theatre, where Bones works over Preston.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Scotty stands by, his lips trembling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Preston opens his eyes, sees Scotty and Kirk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRESTON
{META_DATA}: (faint)
{DIALOGUE}: Is the word given?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (soft)
{DIALOGUE}: The word is given: warp speed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRESTON
{META_DATA}: (almost smiles)
{DIALOGUE}: Aye...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He dies.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pause.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Scotty looks across the body at Kirk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY
{DIALOGUE}: WHY?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (looks at Preston)
{DIALOGUE}: He wants to kill me for passing sentence on him 14 years ago -- and he doesn't care who stands between him and his vengeance.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Scotty, I'm sorry...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY
{DIALOGUE}: He stayed at his post.
{DIALOGUE}: When the trainees ran, he stayed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: If he hadn't, we'd be space by now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Admiral, this is Spock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk hits a wall intercom --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, Spock.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Engine room reports auxiliary power restored.
{DIALOGUE}: We can proceed at impulse power.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (thinks)
{DIALOGUE}: Best speed to Regula I. Kirk out.
{DIALOGUE}: Scotty, I've got to ask: Any chance of getting the mains back on the line?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY
{DIALOGUE}: I dinna think so, sir, but you'll have my best --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With an effort, he gets to his feet --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks -- I know you tried, Doctor...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Squeezes his shoulder and limps off -- We NOW HEAR the sound of impulse power taking effect.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Are you all right?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones shrugs unhappily, looks at Preston.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Doctors lose patients sometimes.
{DIALOGUE}: Damn.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm still in the dark: How'd he know about Genesis?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: At the moment that question takes a back seat to preventing him from laying his hands on it.
{DIALOGUE}: You said it yourself; we're talking about a bang that would re-arrange the universe...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: There may still be time... you gave as good as you got.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (looks him in the eye)
{DIALOGUE}: I got beat.
{DIALOGUE}: We're only alive because I knew something about these ships that he didn't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns and leaves as Bones watches, looks again at Preston.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 107 EXT. SPACE - REGULA I SPACE STATION
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Regula, the dead planet beyond.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 108 EXT. SPACE - ENTERPRISE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Approaching.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As she moves slowly PAST CAMERA, WE PAN WITH her TO SEE that she is approaching the space lab.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 109 INT. BRIDGE - ENTERPRISE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Battle damage, some repaired, some not.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bridge is filled with tension, all hands at station.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Approaching Regula and Space Lab Regula I.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Try again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: Space Station Regular I, this is Starship Enterprise.
{DIALOGUE}: Come in, please...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 110 INT. SPACE STATION REGULAR I - CAROL'S LAB - ON SCREEN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As before, Uhura's image, imploring a response.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: I say again.
{DIALOGUE}: Space Station Regular.
{DIALOGUE}: This is Starship Enterprise.
{DIALOGUE}: Please respond.
{DIALOGUE}: Please respond.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: During this, CAMERA HAS PANNED CLOSE AMONG the techni- cal clutter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then suddenly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOUND -- eerie, frightening.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Our ears cannot place it... and before we can, it is gone a warning.
{META_DATA}: 111 BACK TO BRIDGE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: ... No response, sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Sensors, Captain?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Scanners and sensors still inoperative.
{DIALOGUE}: There's no way to tell what's inside the station.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: And no way of knowing if Reliant is still in the area...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Affirmative, Admiral.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (with irony)
{DIALOGUE}: ... Blind as a Tiberian Bat.
{DIALOGUE}: What do you make of the plantoid beyond?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Regula is class "D'.
{DIALOGUE}: It consists of various remarkable ores.
{DIALOGUE}: Essentially, a great rock in space.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Reliant could be hiding behind that rock.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: A distinct possibility.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Engine room... Scotty, do we have enough power for the transporters?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Just barely, sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (the decision)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm going down to the station.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He starts out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones stops him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Khan could be down there!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: He's BEEN there and hasn't found what he wants.
{DIALOGUE}: Can you spare someone?
{DIALOGUE}: There may be people hurt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: I can spare me...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Begging the Admiral's pardon: General Order 15: 'No flag officer shall beam into a hazardous area without armed escort.'
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: There is no such regulation.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik's gaze falters --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: All right, join the party.
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Spock, the ship is yours.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Aye sir --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Establish a parking orbit around the station and send me a complete damage report when you've talked with Mr. Scott.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Be careful, Jim...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk, Bones and Saavik head for the turbo doors.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 112 EXT. SPACE - SPACE STATION REGULAR I
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSER ANGLE now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The silence is ominous.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 113 INT. SPACE STATION REGULAR I - CAROL'S LAB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: empty, except for the hums and crackles of abandoned equipment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With a FAMILIAR SOUND, BONES, KIRK and SAAVIK MATERIALIZE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All have phasers, communicators and tricorders.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: For a moment they look around, seeing emptiness.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Like being in a haunted house.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Hello...!
{DIALOGUE}: Anybody here?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A WEIRD ECHO reverberates his cries.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{META_DATA}: (raises tricorder)
{DIALOGUE}: Indeterminate life signs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Phasers on stun.
{DIALOGUE}: Move out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They separate.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Each begins to search.
{META_DATA}: 114 ANGLE WITH SAAVIK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She moves to the electronic and data area, examines the consoles, the equipment, then settles for the data bank.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She starts keying sequences with the computer.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 115 INT. SPACE STATION - BONES
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shows signs of fear as he walks through the deserted place, like a scuba diver exploring a cave.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We want him to go back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A NOISE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones reacts with brave apprehension.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rounding a corner, he starts: A RAT scuttles right in front of him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones sighs with relief and moves forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We think he's safe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY SOMETHING FALLS RIGHT ON HIS FACE: an upside down human ARM.
{META_DATA}: 116 SAME LOCALE - LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk helps Bones cut down the last of the five BODIES from where they were hanged, upside down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Having recovered his composure, Bones examines the corpses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We RECOGNIZE Madison, March, among others.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One is clearly the COOK.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (stunned)
{DIALOGUE}: They even killed the galley chief.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: This one looks like a Steward.
{DIALOGUE}: They're not warm, but rigor hasn't set in.
{DIALOGUE}: This didn't happen all that long ago, Jim.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk looks around, despairingly --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Carol...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 117 INT. SPACE LAB DATA BANK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WITH SAAVIK working with console.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Something puzzles her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She frowns, but a NEW SOUND distracts her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks up and moves off.
{META_DATA}: 118 FULL SHOT - IN THE LAB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moan is heard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All three now converge on the area.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As they near it, Saavik's tricorder hums furiously.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Be this a room, a locker of some other place, this time they -- "open the door."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The limp bodies of Chekov and Terrell fall out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (on screen)
{DIALOGUE}: Admiral Kirk, Enterprise.
{DIALOGUE}: Come in, please.
{DIALOGUE}: Come in please.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She will continue sporadically.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: My God!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov emits a live, reassuring moan.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: That's Clark Terrell, Jim, I've served with him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones is passing his medical tricorder over Chekov.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Brain disturbance.
{DIALOGUE}: Appears to be drug induced.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reaches into his kit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shoots Chekov moves off to Terrell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Uhura, voice continues in the b.g.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Saavik, for God's sake, tell her we're all right.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 119 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE - FAVORING UHURA
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: I say again.
{DIALOGUE}: This is Enterprise.
{DIALOGUE}: Please acknowledge signal.
{DIALOGUE}: Please --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik's face appears on her screen.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{META_DATA}: (on screen, hurried)
{DIALOGUE}: Commander Uhura, this is Lt. Saavik.
{DIALOGUE}: We're all right.
{DIALOGUE}: Please stand by.
{DIALOGUE}: Out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{META_DATA}: (baffled)
{DIALOGUE}: Aye, aye.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 120 INT. SPACE STATION - TIGHT GROUP
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov opens his eyes, and stares into Kirk's.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, God, Admiral...!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He weeps like a child, and Kirk holds him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Meanwhile, Terrell opens his eyes and stares at Bones.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: It's Dr. McCoy, Captain.
{DIALOGUE}: Do you remember me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: McCoy?
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, yes.
{META_DATA}: 121 ANGLE FAVORING CHEKOV AND KIRK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov breaks the embrace in high relief and anxiety.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, sir.
{DIALOGUE}: It was Khan!
{DIALOGUE}: We found him on Ceti Alpha V.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Easy, Pavel... Tell me what you can...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: No life signs -- but he was there.
{DIALOGUE}: Captured us.
{DIALOGUE}: He -- he put creatures in our bodies.
{DIALOGUE}: To control our minds.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones takes over Chekov --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: It's all right, you're safe...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: ... Made us say -- lies... Do... things... But we beat him... The Captain and me.
{DIALOGUE}: -- He thought he controlled us, but he didn't ... The Captain was strong.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov breaks into tears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk looks at Terrell, who is more composed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Captain.
{DIALOGUE}: Where is Dr. Marcus?
{DIALOGUE}: Where are the Genesis materials?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: He couldn't find them.
{DIALOGUE}: Some of the scientists were still here, but everything else, even the data banks -- were empty.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: That's true, Admiral.
{DIALOGUE}: All the memory cells have been emptied.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (ponders)
{DIALOGUE}: Erased...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: He tortured those people.
{DIALOGUE}: None of them would tell him anything.
{DIALOGUE}: He went wild, strung them up and slit their throats.
{DIALOGUE}: He wanted to tear the place apart, but he was late: he had to get back to Reliant in time to blow you to bits.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: He came damn close...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: He left us.
{META_DATA}: (with irony)
{DIALOGUE}: We were no longer of use.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Where is the Reliant crew?
{DIALOGUE}: Dead?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: Marooned on Ceti Alpha V. He's completely mad, Admiral.
{DIALOGUE}: He blames you for the death of his wife...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: I know what he blames me for.
{META_DATA}: (thinks)
{DIALOGUE}: The escape pods are all in place.
{META_DATA}: (looks around)
{DIALOGUE}: Where's the transporter room?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 122 INT. SPACE STATION TRANSPORTER ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk, wearing his spectacles, studies the transporter consoles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE WIDENS TO REVEAL the transporter pods, and the others, b.g.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Did he make it down here?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov and Terrell look at each other; they seem a bit stronger.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: It was not my impression.
{DIALOGUE}: He spent most of his time trying to wring the information out of the people.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik approaches Kirk:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Anything?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk looks at her over the rims of the glasses:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Somebody left the unit on.
{DIALOGUE}: If everyone else was dead, it implies that no one remained to turn it off.
{DIALOGUE}: Those people back there bought escape time for Genesis with their lives.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik studies the console.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: It doesn't make sense.
{DIALOGUE}: These coordinates are well within Regula -- a plantoid we know to be lifeless and airless.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (wheels turn)
{DIALOGUE}: If Stage Two was completed, it was underground -- she said it was going to be underground.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Stage Two of what?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk gets it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (on communicator)
{DIALOGUE}: Kirk to Enterprise.
{DIALOGUE}: Damage report, Spock?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Admiral, if we go by the book, like Lieutenant Saavik, hours could seem like days.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I read you, Captain.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's have it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fractional pause.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: The situation is grave, Admiral.
{DIALOGUE}: We won't have main power for six days at least.
{DIALOGUE}: Auxiliary power has temporarily failed, but maybe we can restore that in two days.
{DIALOGUE}: By the book, Admiral.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk frowns.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Meaning you can't even beam us back?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Not at present.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk looks at Saavik and Bones, decides --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Captain Spock, if you do not hear from us within one hour your orders are to restore what power you can, take the Enterprise to the nearest Star Base and alert Starfleet command when you are out of jamming range.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Sir -- we won't leave you behind...!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Uhura, if you don't hear from us, there won't be anybody behind.
{DIALOGUE}: Kirk out.
{META_DATA}: (to Terrell and Chekov)
{DIALOGUE}: You gentleman can remain here, or...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: If it's all the same, Admiral, we'd like to share the risk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (hesitates)
{DIALOGUE}: Very well.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's go.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Go?
{DIALOGUE}: Where are we going?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (points to console)
{DIALOGUE}: Where they went.
{DIALOGUE}: Saavik.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk walks onto the pods as Saavik works the console, rolling in electronic coding.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The others join Kirk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: But what if they went -- nowhere?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Then this will be your big chance to get away from it all.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Ready.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She presses a button, joins them on the pods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Slowly they VANISH.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 123 EXT. SPACE - THE PLANTOID REGULA
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA MOVES TOWARD it as the BEAM SOUND continues, with irregularity.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The plantoid is ugly and dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound frightens us, and climaxes with:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 124 INT. ROCKY CAVERN - REGULA
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The BEAM SOUND screeches, then settles into its comfort- able mode as the FIVE FIGURES FLUCTUATE, FADE, then APPEAR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They look around in wonder and relief.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Admiral --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She indicates something O.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They cross as CAMERA reveals a cave wall stacked with technical materials and crowned by a LARGE PROJECTILE, a giant version of the model we saw earlier.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They stare.
{META_DATA}: (N.B. FEATURE GENESIS ARMING CONTROL BOX.)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Genesis, I presume.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They walk by a group of crates.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It all happens very fast: David leaps out and tackles Kirk, throwing him to the ground and landing atop him, a knife at his throat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At the same time, Bones and Saavik reach for their phasers, but Jedda, already armed, steps out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He has them covered and helpless.
{META_DATA}: 125 ANGLE FAVORING DAVID
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: You're the sonavabitch who committed mass murder up there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He raises the knife --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: I'm Admiral Kirk...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: We were still there, you dumb bastard!
{DIALOGUE}: We could hear the screams all the way to the transporter room --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Again he raises the knife --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Where's Dr. Marcus --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: I'm Doctor Marcus!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carol reaches the tunnel entrance to the cave --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: David --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Mother, go back!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carol sees Kirk --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: Jim --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Go back.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm going to kill him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{META_DATA}: (takes a breath)
{DIALOGUE}: You do that and you'll have murdered your father.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All react.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: David and Kirk, facing each other, are turned to stone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones, Jedda and Chekov turn to look at Carol, wondering.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell very casually takes the phaser from Jedda.
{META_DATA}: 126 NEW ANGLE (FORMERLY SCENE 134)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{META_DATA}: (cool)
{DIALOGUE}: I'll hold onto this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But Kirk and Carol ignore them and walk towards each other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There are tears in Carol's eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She reaches up, trying to smile and touches his hair --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: You've got a little grey --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She can't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk takes her and holds her tightly, look- ing at David, over her shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stands there, stunned, looking back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Carol.
{DIALOGUE}: Is that true?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She nods --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Why didn't you tell me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: She's making it up!
{DIALOGUE}: My father was Professor --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: David, you're just making this harder --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: I'm afraid it's even harder than you think, Doctor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He and Chekov have their phasers trained on them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Please don't move --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Chekov -- !
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry, Admiral.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell speaks into his wrist recorder.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: Your excellency, have you been listening?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (filtered)
{DIALOGUE}: I have indeed, Captain.
{DIALOGUE}: You have done well...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: I knew it -- !
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: David makes a reckless break for Terrell; Saavik instantly throws herself on him bringing him down as Terrell fires, hitting Jedda, who was behind David -- a killing ray.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jedda dematerializes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carol SCREAMS and David reacts with horror and guilt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Most importantly, Chekov begins to tremble.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell himself is shaken by his reflexive action.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's in semi-panic.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: Don't move -- any of you!
{META_DATA}: 127 thru thru 134
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 135 EXT. SPACE - THE DARK SIDE OF REGULA
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reliant, motionless in a parking orbit.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 136 INT. RELIANT BRIDGE - FAVORING KHAN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Joachim over his shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Others in evidence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Khan speaks into his console.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Captain... We're waiting.
{DIALOGUE}: What's the delay?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 137 INT. ROCKY CAVERN (INTERCUT AS DESIRED)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: All is well, sir.
{DIALOGUE}: You have the coordinates to beam up Genesis...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: First things first, Captain.
{DIALOGUE}: Kill Admiral Kirk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reactions by all -- only Kirk and Bones are unsurprised.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: David and Saavik, dazed, fight the urge to do something.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov is close to a seizure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell fights conflicting mental signals.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERRELL
{DIALOGUE}: Excellency... it is difficult.
{DIALOGUE}: I try to obey, but --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Kill him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As though tearing off a leach, Terrell grabs at the wrist recorder and flings it to the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A shock- wave of pain hits Terrell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He recovers, trembling and tries to obey.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov is shaking badly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell aims his phaser at Kirk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov slowly raises his phaser and aims at Terrell, though his hands are like lead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We THINK Chekov is going to do the right thing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then, shockingly: Terrell turns his phaser on himself.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (still emanates from wrist recorder)
{DIALOGUE}: Kill him, Terrell.
{DIALOGUE}: Now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terrell does, blowing himself into oblivion.
{META_DATA}: 138 ANGLE - FAVORING CHEKOV
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He SCREAMS, horribly, drops his phaser, clutching his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones leaps to his side, pulls an injection device from his belt pack, jabs it into Chekov's arm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chekov, almost with a sigh of relief, drops.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Terrell?
{DIALOGUE}: Chekov -- !
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Jim -- for God's sake!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They rush to his side, as do Carol and David.
{META_DATA}: 139 ANGLE - FAVORING CHEKOV
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: From the fallen man's ear, something begins to emerge.
{META_DATA}: 140 VERY CLOSE - CHEKOV'S EAR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Ceti eel crawls out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It has grown quite large.
{META_DATA}: 141 SCENE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Horror from all.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk picks up a phaser.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the eel clears Chekov, he fires and destroys it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shudders, then sees the wrist recorder and grabs it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Khan, you bloodsucker, they're finished!
{DIALOGUE}: You'll have to do your own dirty work now.
{DIALOGUE}: Do you hear me?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 142 INT. RELIANT BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Khan reacts to Kirk's VOICE: electronic shock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He clutches the communicator, his eye-whites rolling.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Kirk!
{DIALOGUE}: Kirk, you are still alive -- my old friend...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INTERCUT AS DESIRED WITH
{META_DATA}: 143 ROCKY CAVERN - FAVORING KIRK
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Still, 'old friend.'
{DIALOGUE}: You've managed to kill just about everyone else, but like a poor marksman, you keep missing the target.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (ironic)
{DIALOGUE}: Perhaps I no longer need to try.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He punches several buttons.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the Rocky Cavern the transporter beam locks on to the Genesis torpedo and its arming control box.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Kirk and the others watch, horrified, Khan beams up the materials.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: David tries to reach the torpedo, but Saavik holds him fast --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Let go -- he can't -- !
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Only half of you would get there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The beam disappears and Genesis with it, leaving them alone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (desperate)
{DIALOGUE}: Khan, you have Genesis, but you don't have me!
{DIALOGUE}: You were going to kill me, Khan, it was your sole purpose.
{DIALOGUE}: You'll have to come down here to do it!
{DIALOGUE}: You'll have to come down!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: I've done far worse than kill you, Admiral.
{DIALOGUE}: I've hurt you.
{DIALOGUE}: And I wish to go on hurting you.
{DIALOGUE}: I shall leave you, as you left me -- where no one will ever find you: poetic justice; marooned for eternity in the center of a dead planet -- buried alive.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Khan -- !
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: Goodbye, Admiral.
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, and don't count on Enterprise.
{DIALOGUE}: She can't move.
{DIALOGUE}: My next act will be to blow her out of the heavens.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: KHAN!
{META_DATA}: 144 OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 145 INT. RELIANT BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Khan closes his eyes in voluptuous satisfaction.
