{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: It's a long story.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: We appear to have plenty of time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{META_DATA}: (dry)
{DIALOGUE}: You and your father can catch up on things.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{META_DATA}: (bitter)
{DIALOGUE}: My father.
{DIALOGUE}: I hope you realize another man has just been killed because of...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Because of you, son.
{DIALOGUE}: You shouldn't have tried to rush someone holding a primed phaser.
{DIALOGUE}: Anyway it isn't one man dead, it's two, in case you've lost count.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: David has been effectively spiked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Long silence.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Do you have anything to eat?
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know about anyone else, but I'm starved.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: How can you think of food at a time like this?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Our first order of business is survival.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: There's food in the Genesis cave, enough to last a lifetime -- should that be necessary.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: We thought this was Genesis.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carol laughs -- there's an edge of hysteria to it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: This?
{DIALOGUE}: It took the Starfleet corps of engineers ten months in space suits to tunnel out all this.
{DIALOGUE}: What we did in there -- we did in a day.
{DIALOGUE}: David, why don't you show Dr. McCoy and the Lieutenant our idea of food.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: But we can't just sit here -- !
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (unruffled)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, yes we can.
{DIALOGUE}: Is there really something to eat?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: David looks at his father, who checks his watch, putting on his spectacles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: David.
{DIALOGUE}: Please.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{META_DATA}: (to Kirk)
{DIALOGUE}: This is just to give us something to do, isn't it?
