{DIALOGUE}: Surrender and prepare to be boarded.
{DIALOGUE}: Repeat...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In f.g., chillingly, Khan rises INTO SHOT by the main console.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is horribly burned, and it is clear that he is clinging to life by his will.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: No... Kirk.
{DIALOGUE}: The game's not over.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Uhura's voice continues O.S., Khan pulls himself into a chair at the console, one of his hands useless at his side.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: To the last I will grapple with thee!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Painfully, with one good arm, he starts arming the Genesis console.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 213A INT. RELIANT TRANSPORTER ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There sits the Genesis torpedo: lights start blinking in response.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As we watch, the CHILD we met on Ceti Alpha walks to the torpedo and smiles at the lights.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 214 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: UHURA
{DIALOGUE}: Enterprise to Reliant: you are ordered to surrender your vessel.
{DIALOGUE}: Respond!
{META_DATA}: (to Kirk)
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing, sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: We'll beam aboard.
{DIALOGUE}: Alert transporter room --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Admiral.
{DIALOGUE}: Scanning an energy source on Reliant.
{DIALOGUE}: A pattern I've never seen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: David peers closer over Spock's shoulder, reacts.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: It's the Genesis Wave!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: He's on a build up to detonation!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: How soon --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: We encoded four minutes --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: We'll beam aboard and stop it --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: You can't!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The briefest stunned moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk hits intercom:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Scotty, I need warp speed in three minutes or we're all dead!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: STATIC.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Scotty!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock leaps from his place and disappears through the bridge doors.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Saavik, get us out, best speed!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Aye, sir.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 215 EXT. SPACE NEBULA
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Enterprise backs away from Reliant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her speed is pain- fully slow.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 216 INT. RELIANT BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON SCREEN, Enterprise, intermittent image, backs away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Khan smiles triumphantly through his pain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An elec- tronic power SOUND has been building.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KHAN
{DIALOGUE}: No... You can't get away... From hell's heart I stab at thee...
{META_DATA}: (amid the pain)
{DIALOGUE}: For hate's sake... I spit my last breath at thee!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Khan topples forward, dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The WHINE continues to build chillingly.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 217 INT. ENTERPRISE ENGINE ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock rushes in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones ministers to Scotty, b.g.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock sizes up the situation, starts for the radiation room, Bones intercepts him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Are you out of your Vulcan mind?
{DIALOGUE}: No human can tolerate the radiation loose in there!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: But, as you are so fond of observing, Doctor, I'm not human.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: You're not going in there -- !
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: I'm afraid I can't stop to discuss this logically --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gives Bones the Vulcan nerve pinch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones goes down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock presses the access button and enters the Reactor Room, a separated area behind radiation-proof glass and metal, RED FLASHING LIGHTS and an iridescent blue glow within.
{META_DATA}: 218 ANGLE - SCOTTY AND BONES
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY
{META_DATA}: (in horror)
{DIALOGUE}: Spock -- get out of there!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 219 INT. ENTERPRISE REACTOR ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bathed in blue light, arcing energy around him, Spock is a silhouetted figure as he goes to work, door clos- ing behind him.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 220 EXT. SPACE - RELIANT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The WHINE increasing, the dead ship Reliant alive with danger...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 221 EXT. SPACE NEBULA - ENTERPRISE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A snail's pace compared to the escape speed needed.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 222 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Time from my mark...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Two minutes, ten seconds.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (intercom)
{DIALOGUE}: Engine room!
{DIALOGUE}: What's happening?!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 223 INT. ENTERPRISE REACTOR ROOM (INTERCUT AS REQUIRED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Outside the glass, Scotty and Bones screaming:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY
{DIALOGUE}: Captain, please!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: Get out!
{DIALOGUE}: Get out, man!
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, dear God...!
{META_DATA}: 224 WITHIN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE CAN SEE the silent urging of Bones and Scotty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock is oblivious.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Amid the fire-blue arcs, he moves to the control panel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Between his hands and the con- trols, power arcs insanely.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock is in an inferno, a radiation hell, fighting now with all his strength to control it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Slowly, the damping rods move out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock moves to a manual control, begins to turn it.
{META_DATA}: 225 CLOSE - SPOCK'S HANDS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: on the manual control, slowly turning black.
{META_DATA}: 226 HIS FACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His face, using all the self discipline he is capable of to control the pain, continuing to work --
{META_DATA}: 227 WITHOUT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones and Scotty react in helpless horror.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 228 EXT. SPACE NEBULA
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Enterprise still well within the nebula, Reliant a figure still visible in b.g. She's crawling still.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 229 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reliant, now symbol of death, ON SCREEN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Time!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Three minutes, thirty seconds.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Distance from Reliant...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHEKOV
{DIALOGUE}: Four hundred kilometers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk looks at David, but David shakes his head: No way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CADET
{DIALOGUE}: Sir!
{DIALOGUE}: The mains are back on line -- !
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Bless you, Scotty.
{DIALOGUE}: Go, Saavik!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She increases power and --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 230 EXT. SPACE NEBULA - SERIES OF SHOTS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A) With a burst of warp speed, Enterprise accelerates out of the lazy pace and whooshes PUT OF SCENE, leaving Reliant behind.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: B) POV RELIANT
{META_DATA}: disappearing in the swirls of:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: C) POV MUTARA NEBULA
{META_DATA}: which clears the flame and --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: D) ENTERPRISE
{META_DATA}: roaring through space -- and:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: E) RELIANT
{META_DATA}: The WHINE increases to fever pitch, then: she goes!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: F) EXT. MUTARA NEBULA - MASTER EFFECT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Reliant goes, so goes the nebula.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The "Genesis Effect" WE SAW in its earliest experiments, now seems familiar on a gigantic, cosmic scale.
{META_DATA}: The blinding flash at first, followed by the same tumbling turbulence of the miniature test. It is awesome.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 231 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bridge doors open and Carol appears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Instinctively she draws near her son.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally, Kirk turns, sees Carol --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Reduce speed.
{DIALOGUE}: My God, Carl.
{DIALOGUE}: Look at it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON SCREEN and INTERCUT -- GENESIS TUMBLES and starts evolving.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moment in history.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing, on intercom)
{DIALOGUE}: Engine Room.
{DIALOGUE}: Well done.
{DIALOGUE}: Scotty?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES' VOICE
{META_DATA}: (after a beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Jim, you'd better get down here.
{DIALOGUE}: Hurry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tone frightens Kirk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Saavik, take the con.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He moves through the doors quickly, leaving the rest staring at the new world evolving.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 232 INT. STAIRWAY TO ENGINE ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is endless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk runs forever, feet pounding down, down, down --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 233 EXT. SPACE AND ON SCREEN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The clouds tumble and move, new things lie beyond --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 234 INT. STAIRS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk races --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 235 INT. ENTERPRISE ENGINE ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk emerges to encounter Scotty and Bones.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their looks tell him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sees the flashing light over the Reactor Room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He dashes for the control panel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones grabs him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCOTTY
{DIALOGUE}: No, sir!
{DIALOGUE}: You'll flood the whole compartment...!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: He'll die -- !
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{META_DATA}: (also holds him)
{DIALOGUE}: He's dead already, Jim.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk's eyes bulge.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, God.
{META_DATA}: 236 ANGLE AT REACTOR ROOM GLASS DOOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With stunned understanding, Kirk stumbles to the door, sees Spock on his knees, hands blackened, face cracked with radiation lines and scars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock shakes his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With a feeble hand he reaches the intercom button: filtered communication.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Spock!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: The ship -- out of danger?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Yes --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock is satisfied; he fights for breath --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Don't grieve, Admiral -- it's logical: the good of the many outweighs --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He almost keels over.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk has tears streaming down his face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: ... the good of the few...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Or the one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He props a hand on the glass to support himself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk's hand reflexively goes to match Spock's on the other side of the glass --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: I never took the Kobayashi Maru test -- until now.
{DIALOGUE}: What do you think of my solution?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Spock...!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK
{DIALOGUE}: I have been -- and always will be -- your friend... Live.
{DIALOGUE}: Long.
{DIALOGUE}: And.
{DIALOGUE}: Prosper.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock falls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones and Scotty react.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: No...!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (intercom)
{DIALOGUE}: Admiral, you've got to see this!
{DIALOGUE}: There's new life -- a whole new world, a Genesis world -- !
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But Kirk is past hearing or caring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is huddled up against the glass, destroyed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones looks on, helpless.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 237 EXT. SPACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A spectacular look at Carol's planet being born!
{META_DATA}: 238 OMITTED
{META_DATA}: 239 CAMERA PULLS BACK TO REVEAL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the Ship's Company in full dress uniforms assembled for ship's burial service.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Over the PULLBACK, we HEAR:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: In accordance with the traditions of Starfleet and of Article 184 Starfleet Regulations, we are assembled here today to pay final respects to our honored dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carol and David are PROMINENTLY FEATURED.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: David watching Kirk attentively.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: So are Sulu, Uhura, Chekov, and Saavik.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bones stands next to Kirk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Scotty carries his bagpipes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik wears her hair down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: And yet, in the midst of our sorrow it should be noted that this death takes place in the shadow of new life, the sunrise of a new world, a world that our beloved comrade gave his own life to protect and nourish.
{DIALOGUE}: He did not feel that sacrifice a vain or empty one -- and we will not debate his profound wisdom, in these proceedings.
{DIALOGUE}: Of my friend, I can only say this, that of all the souls I have encountered in my travels, his was the most --
{META_DATA}: (he falters)
{DIALOGUE}: -- human.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tries to go on, but catches Bones' face: Bones is streaming tears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk can't go on.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Lieutenant Saavik.
{META_DATA}: 240 OMITTED
{META_DATA}: 241 ANGLE - THE GROUP
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik steps forward.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: We commend the soul of our brother departed.
{DIALOGUE}: We love we commit his body to the depths of space.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: Honors -- hup!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All Starfleet personnel salute.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Scotty begins to PIPE, an odd blare which mellows into Amazing Grace.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk nods a signal.
{META_DATA}: 242 THE CAPSULE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A gleaming black projectile is carried by pallbearers into the launching chamber, which locks behind it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At a hand signal from a TORPEDOMAN, the projectile is fired.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NOISE.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 243 EXT. SPACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spock's remains seen on their way to the new world.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The capsule grows too small to SEE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bagpipes STOP.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 244 INT. TORPEDO ROOM
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SULU
{DIALOGUE}: Return -- hup!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The salute drop.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Lieutenant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She steps to him and they exchange salutes --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing; very quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: After you dismiss the company, you will take the watch.
{DIALOGUE}: Set course for Ceti Alpha V and we'll pick up survivors.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Aye, sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: I'll be in my quarters if needed, but I would prefer...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Understood, sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (aloud)
{DIALOGUE}: Dismiss the company.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They salute.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She about-faces as Kirk walks towards the Turbo Lift.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik issues dismissal and posting orders, but WE TRUCK with Kirk until CAMERA STOPS and he leaves FRAME and WE HOLD on David.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He finally understands.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 245 INT. KIRK'S QUARTERS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a long moment, the CAMERA DISCOVERS Kirk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pours a drink, then decides not to have it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sits wearily, not knowing how to shake the ghosts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then he sees the book.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk picks up the battered volume, the gift from his friend, and closes his eyes a moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Almost idly he starts turning pages, looking for a clue.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But he can't see the writing -- he rummages through his pockets and pulls out the half-glasses --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One of the lenses is broken.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It has a deep impact on Kirk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He puts down the book and glasses and covers his eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SOFT BONG.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk clears his throat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Yes... come.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door whooshes open and closes to admit David.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The last person Kirk expected to see.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: I don't mean to intrude.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Uh, no...
{META_DATA}: (rises)
{DIALOGUE}: I should be on the bridge.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Are you running away from me?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: David's strength is turning a corner with Kirk --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: I suppose I was.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: I poured a drink.
{DIALOGUE}: Would you like it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: I -- I guess I'm not what you expected.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (rueful)
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't expect anything.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: That makes two of us.
{META_DATA}: (he studies his father)
{DIALOGUE}: Lieutenant Saavik was right: you never have faced death --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (hoarse)
{DIALOGUE}: Not like this -- no.
{DIALOGUE}: I haven't faced death, I cheated death.
{DIALOGUE}: I tricked my way out of death and patted myself on the back for my ingenuity.
{DIALOGUE}: I know nothing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: You knew enough to tell Saavik that how we face death is at least as important as how we face life --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: It was just words.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: But good words.
{DIALOGUE}: That's where ideas begin.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe you should listen to them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: I'm trying, David.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: So am I. My friends were killed, too.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: I am truly sorry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pause.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They study each other.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: I was wrong about you.
{DIALOGUE}: And I'm sorry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Is that what you came here to say?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Mainly.
{META_DATA}: (he starts out, then turns -- )
{DIALOGUE}: And also that I'm proud -- very proud -- to be your son.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A stunned moment, then Kirk lets it all hang out: for David, for Carol and for Spock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hugs his son, hold- ing onto him as if to life itself.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 246 EXT. SPACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Enterprise passes the new planet in all its beauty.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 247 INT. ENTERPRISE BRIDGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door whooshes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk strides on the bridge, David with him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carol is there with Bones; they are glad at what they see.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Admiral on the bridge!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: As you were, Mr. Saavik.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Aye, sir.
{DIALOGUE}: On course to Ceti Alpha.
{DIALOGUE}: All is well.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Good, I believe you already know my, uh, son --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saavik comes close to blushing --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, well, why don't you show him around and...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{DIALOGUE}: Aye, sir --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She takes him off, deadpan amusement --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: So you turn out to be the dumb bastard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They stare at her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAAVIK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: That is a little joke.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kirk has a smile.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He joins Bones and Carol facing the screen.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: She's changed her hair again.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Will you look at that?
{DIALOGUE}: Think they'll name it for you, Doctor?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{DIALOGUE}: Not if I can help it.
{DIALOGUE}: We'll name it for our friend.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: It is a far far better thing I do than I have ever done before... a far better resting place I go to than I have ever known...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROL
{META_DATA}: (soft)
{DIALOGUE}: Is that a poem?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{DIALOGUE}: Something Spock was trying to tell me.
{DIALOGUE}: On my birthday.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shakes his head, remembering --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BONES
{DIALOGUE}: You okay, Jim?
{DIALOGUE}: How do you feel?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (considers; smiles)
{DIALOGUE}: Young.
{DIALOGUE}: I feel young, Doctor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns to Saavik and David --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KIRK
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Lieutenant, new course: 'Second star to the right and straight on till morning.'
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bridge crackles with lights and CHATTER as we...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{META_DATA}: 247A THE VIEWSCREEN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AND GO THROUGH TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 248 EXT. SPACE FINALE (BOARDED)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SPOCK'S VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Space, the final frontier... These are the continuing voyages of the Starship Enterprise... Her ongoing mission: to explore strange new worlds... to seek out new life and new civilizations... To boldly go where no man has gone before...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is moving out now, passing CAMERA and heading toward the distant stars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is beautiful and they are beautiful.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And as she slowly disappears from VIEW...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MUSIC RISES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CREDITS ROLL.
{META_DATA}: THE END
